baseline_groups.claim_summary: The Alaska PFD does not significantly reduce employment rates.
baseline_groups.notes: Three comparison groups. ak_vs_wa has NaN SE (2 clusters). Coefficients near-zero (~2.5e-08). Paper SCM: +0.010 (p=0.39).

baseline_groups.claim_summary: The Alaska PFD increases part-time employment rates.
The Alaska PFD has a small negative effect on labor force participation.
baseline_groups.notes: Coefficients -0.001 to -0.007. Paper SCM: -0.005 (p=0.22). ak_vs_wa has NaN SE.

baseline_groups.claim_summary: The Alaska PFD reduces hours worked per week.
baseline_groups.notes: MORG data, 1979-2014. Coefficients -2.00 and -1.64. Paper SCM: -1.23 (p=0.05).

global_notes: 57/134 specs have empty p-values (2-state models with NaN SE). Some employed coefs ~1e-08 with R2~1.0 (collinearity). post_1985 has implausibly large coef (0.20). oil/vs_oil_states duplicates comparison_oil_states. Four outcomes = four baseline claims.
